Everything's pressing.

23:23.624 --> 23:26.050
Everything's got to have my attention right now.

23:26.130 --> 23:27.413
I've got to do it right now.

23:27.553 --> 23:29.738
Today, it can't wait until tomorrow.

23:29.979 --> 23:31.462
I have to deal with it now.

23:31.783 --> 23:36.914
One of the most common barriers to neighboring is just busyness.

23:37.058 --> 23:44.388
In our fast-paced world, our schedules become so full that we barely have time for ourselves, let alone anybody else.

23:44.428 --> 23:54.101
We rush from one task to the next, checking items off of our to-do list, all while missing the opportunities that are right in front of us to connect with those around us.

23:55.824 --> 24:06.098
Proverbs 27, 10 tells us to not forsake your friend or a friend of the family, implying that relationships require time and attention.

24:09.474 --> 24:15.541
Yet in the hustle and bustle of life, we often let these relationships kind of slide.

24:17.223 --> 24:18.344
Listen, it's not out of malice.

24:18.384 --> 24:19.365
It's not out of being ugly.

24:19.385 --> 24:21.087
It's not caring.

24:21.127 --> 24:24.351
It's simply because we're busy.

24:24.932 --> 24:27.274
We don't realize that three days has gone by.

24:27.535 --> 24:29.777
I'm going to tell you a quick story on myself.

24:30.858 --> 24:32.200
My mom, she's my grandma.

24:32.240 --> 24:32.741
You know that.

24:32.821 --> 24:33.682
I was raised by my grandma.

24:33.702 --> 24:34.242
I call her mom.

24:35.384 --> 24:37.586
She calls me just about every day.

24:38.722 --> 24:41.445
Hey, you haven't called me in X number of days.

24:41.505 --> 24:42.847
Mom, I talked to you yesterday.

24:44.489 --> 24:51.597
Or in the busyness, sometimes, either in meetings or whatever it is, I'll have to hit ignore.

24:51.658 --> 24:54.962
Don't do that to your parents, kids.

24:56.303 --> 24:57.044
I'm a bad son.

24:57.845 --> 24:58.486
Not really, but.

24:59.928 --> 25:05.935
And sometimes, and I'll call her back later and I'll say, hey, mom, I'm so sorry that I had to cancel your call.

25:05.975 --> 25:08.658
I was in the middle of a meeting, blah, blah, blah, whatever it is.

25:09.826 --> 25:19.618
And she will inevitably, and moms, please don't do this, inevitably, she will say, well, you're just too busy for me anymore.

25:22.322 --> 25:23.283
Yeah, mom, that's it.

25:23.563 --> 25:24.565
I'm too busy for you.

25:26.367 --> 25:27.088
But it happens.

25:27.428 --> 25:32.114
So even for the best of us or the worst of us, whichever one you want to classify me in,

25:32.738 --> 25:33.479
We get busy.

25:33.519 --> 25:36.402
We don't realize how much time has passed.

25:36.422 --> 25:42.047
We don't realize before a week has gone by and you're like, oh, I was gonna call sister so-and-so.

25:42.347 --> 25:46.171
I was gonna touch base with this person or that person.

25:46.211 --> 25:50.715
I was gonna call my mom or my dad or my auntie or my uncle or whatever it may be.

25:52.357 --> 25:56.221
And we allow busyness to get us wrapped up.

25:57.942 --> 26:01.906
Again, we have a great story about this in scripture in Luke chapter 10.

26:03.778 --> 26:07.005
verses 38 to 42 of Mary and Martha.

26:07.025 --> 26:12.417
This is that tension of I want to sit at the feet of Jesus, but there's stuff to do.

26:12.818 --> 26:13.460
We're busy.

26:13.500 --> 26:14.222
We've got to do.

26:14.262 --> 26:16.667
We've got to be and we've got to make it happen.

26:18.210 --> 26:19.794
But what does Jesus tell her?

26:19.970 --> 26:33.527
tell them when all of it kind of comes to a head and kind of explodes and Martha was busy with the preparations and Mary chose to sit at Jesus' feet and she chooses to prioritize relationship over tasks.

26:33.948 --> 26:48.626
Jesus gently, say that word, gently, okay, gently rebukes Martha telling her that Mary's chosen what is a better way.

26:50.562 --> 27:01.295
We've got to learn to prioritize our relationships with our neighbors, over the endless tasks that pull for our attention.

27:02.237 --> 27:07.623
If I might give you a leadership moment, margin.

27:08.805 --> 27:14.131
If you're a note-taker, write that word down in the margin of your notes, margin.

27:15.854 --> 27:19.378
Too many of us do not have margin in our life.

27:19.746 --> 27:21.068
We don't have it in our schedules.

27:21.108 --> 27:22.350
We don't have it in our budgets.

27:22.671 --> 27:33.288
So our budgets are stretched so tight that when the hot water heater breaks, there's no money for, when a tire goes flat and you just have to get a patch, there's no money for it.

27:33.308 --> 27:40.960
When a situation in life happens and somebody gets sick, we don't have, oh, what am I gonna do?

27:41.802 --> 27:44.466
Because we've not built any margin into our life.

27:45.026 --> 27:53.274
This is kind of the crux of what we're trying to get at when we talk about the barriers to neighboring is we don't have any margin.

27:53.515 --> 27:57.659
Listen, I would love to stop and talk to, how many neighbors do we have?

27:57.679 --> 28:04.085
I can't even count because we have apartment buildings, but I would love to spend my days talking to all the neighbors.

28:05.947 --> 28:09.671
But then we would just stand here and stare at each other for about 40 minutes, right?

28:10.271 --> 28:12.914
Because I wouldn't have time to prep this and I wouldn't.

28:14.178 --> 28:18.042
There's balance, but we've got to find margin.

28:19.083 --> 28:21.105
Another barriers fear or indifference.

28:22.186 --> 28:23.807
It's the discomfort of the unknown.

28:23.887 --> 28:25.509
We don't know the neighbor.

28:25.549 --> 28:26.530
We haven't got to know them.

28:26.630 --> 28:31.995
I've lived in this whatever house or whatever apartment and I've never gotten to know my neighbor.

28:34.198 --> 28:42.866
But see, Philippians chapter two, verses three and four tells us to look past these fears.

28:43.234 --> 28:46.317
Don't look out only for your own interests, but take an interest in others.

28:48.099 --> 28:50.100
Look past these situations.

28:50.120 --> 28:53.944
Look past the fears because fear is always rooted in the unknown.

28:53.984 --> 28:58.108
When I get fearful, when I get stressed out, it's because I don't know what's coming next.

28:58.468 --> 28:59.730
I don't worry about what I know.

28:59.750 --> 29:03.353
I don't worry about what I'm familiar with.

29:03.393 --> 29:09.198
How do you start the conversation?

29:09.779 --> 29:10.960
What if they don't like me?

29:11.320 --> 29:13.042
What if they're an anti-Christian?

29:13.442 --> 29:14.383
Okay, the more and more.

29:14.684 --> 29:18.949
So used to, there used to be a day where we could come up and talk about, well, yeah, I go to church.

29:18.969 --> 29:20.210
Oh, really, where do you go to church?

29:20.251 --> 29:21.132
I go to church too.

29:21.152 --> 29:24.836
And all those niceties, even if they didn't, they were at least cordial.

29:25.858 --> 29:28.421
Now it's like, oh, I'm a believer in Christ.

29:28.441 --> 29:29.863
I don't wanna hear about it.

29:31.204 --> 29:32.486
Or how stupid are you?

29:34.148 --> 29:35.229
And we don't know.

29:35.429 --> 29:39.434
And so we're a little bit afraid to get into those kinds of conversations.

29:40.215 --> 29:42.258
And the enemy's sitting there going,

29:42.594 --> 29:43.496
you don't want to do that.

29:47.307 --> 29:54.506
But the gospel calls us to care deeply enough about others that we reflect Christ back.

29:55.629 --> 29:57.394
What is the passage no longer I but

29:58.146 --> 29:59.468
Christ that lives within me.

29:59.808 --> 30:01.550
So it's not me making the approach.

30:01.931 --> 30:04.354
It's Jesus saying, hey, I want you to talk to this person.

30:04.714 --> 30:06.456
I want you to move past the barrier.

30:06.476 --> 30:09.140
I want you to move past the situation.

30:09.420 --> 30:10.421
And I want you to move in.

30:10.682 --> 30:12.164
And I want you to make a connection.

30:12.424 --> 30:15.388
Because I have already sent the Holy Spirit.

30:15.408 --> 30:17.130
I've already prepared the field.

30:17.350 --> 30:19.012
I've already sent workers in.

30:19.292 --> 30:20.894
And they've done all the prep work.

30:20.934 --> 30:22.877
And I need you to harvest.

30:24.419 --> 30:26.962
How many of us have missed the harvest?

30:27.810 --> 30:28.250
It happens.

30:29.732 --> 30:43.047
But how many of us have missed being the catalyst for somebody's relationship with Christ because we were a little bit afraid of talking to them either because of what they look like, a big old burly biker guy or whatever it is.

30:48.233 --> 30:49.294
Because what does Jesus say?

30:49.314 --> 30:56.242
He says, you know the saying, four months between planting and harvest, but I say, wake up and look around.

30:57.122 --> 30:59.267
The fields are ready and ripe for harvest.

31:01.132 --> 31:01.753
Who's going to go?

31:01.814 --> 31:08.530
Who's going to do what is necessary in the book, the art of neighboring

31:08.610 --> 31:14.236
there is a group of neighbors that discovered they were all too busy to know each other.

31:14.756 --> 31:21.123
And it wasn't until they intentionally decided to slow down and make time for real relationship to begin to form.

31:21.343 --> 31:27.149
They moved past the barriers of busyness and fear, choosing instead to invest in their community.

31:27.169 --> 31:32.315
And what they found was that neighboring didn't just benefit those they reached out to.

31:32.355 --> 31:35.698
It actually transformed their own lives.

31:36.706 --> 31:38.868
Our lives are richer when we have community.

31:38.888 --> 31:40.330
We've spoken about that before.

31:43.473 --> 31:43.954
Number three.

31:46.737 --> 31:51.281
So let's look at some practical steps of what it is to become a good neighbor.

31:52.443 --> 31:56.187
Look at Romans chapter 12 and verses nine to 13.

31:56.207 --> 32:00.271
It says, don't just pretend to love others.

32:02.453 --> 32:03.314
Really love them.

32:04.322 --> 32:08.049
So that's not a qualifying thing that Pastor Mike added to the Word of God.

32:09.693 --> 32:13.500
This is what's in, if you open your paper Bible or your digital Bible, this is what's in there.

32:13.520 --> 32:15.945
It says, don't just pretend to love others, really love them.

32:16.626 --> 32:20.434
He's going, hey, hello, pay attention.

32:21.154 --> 32:29.484
Really love them, hate what is wrong, hold tightly to what is good, love each other with genuine affection and take delight in honoring each other.

32:29.945 --> 32:34.070
Never be lazy but work hard and serve the Lord enthusiastically.

32:34.571 --> 32:36.473
Rejoice in our confident hope.

32:36.733 --> 32:39.717
Be patient in trouble and keep on praying.

32:39.997 --> 32:43.261
When God's people are in need, be ready to help them.

32:43.502 --> 32:47.026
Always be eager to practice hospitality.

32:49.314 --> 32:50.255
So what are we supposed to do?

32:50.275 --> 32:51.537
We're supposed to be intentional.

32:52.618 --> 32:54.601
We don't have to do great big things.

32:54.661 --> 32:56.163
It's not about grand gestures.

32:56.443 --> 32:59.547
It starts with small intentional actions.

33:00.889 --> 33:06.917
When Paul, when he says, practice hospitality, this is just a starting point.

33:07.197 --> 33:09.861
But it doesn't have to mean that you host a big dinner party.

33:10.041 --> 33:11.623
You don't have to have everybody over at your house.

33:11.683 --> 33:13.265
And you're like, we have kids.

33:14.086 --> 33:17.010
Don't come to our house to mess.

33:17.346 --> 33:19.328
And like Tuesdays is our cleaning day.

33:19.349 --> 33:20.530
So if you want to come, come then.

33:21.812 --> 33:24.215
I'm kidding, but maybe.

33:27.238 --> 33:28.740
You don't have to invite everybody over.

33:28.901 --> 33:30.102
This isn't what this is about.

33:33.166 --> 33:35.609
This is about simply doing small gestures.

33:35.709 --> 33:36.490
Good morning, Tom.

33:36.830 --> 33:37.712
Good morning, Sally.

33:39.894 --> 33:40.996
Hey, how are you doing today?

33:42.598 --> 33:46.002
Hey, I noticed you missed taking

33:46.210 --> 33:47.652
How many of you love HOAs?

33:47.672 --> 33:49.755
I mean, they live in one, okay?

33:50.496 --> 33:55.363
If you love HOAs, I need you to come to the altar because I'm gonna pray for you, okay?

33:56.625 --> 34:00.190
I despise HOAs, I'm just gonna be very honest, okay?

34:00.210 --> 34:05.557
Because there's never been an HOA that I've ever been part of or heard about that actually ran well.

34:06.138 --> 34:09.343
And I'll be honest with you, I was the president of an HOA for a little while.

34:10.084 --> 34:14.450
And I was the president for all of about one month.

34:14.946 --> 34:17.068
And I said, oh, these people are crazy.

34:17.108 --> 34:18.009
I ain't doing this no more.

34:18.950 --> 34:22.994
And then the new president came and mowed my lawn because I didn't mow it fast enough.

34:23.014 --> 34:24.295
And I said, don't do that anymore.

34:27.378 --> 34:28.239
It's not about that.

34:28.299 --> 34:35.365
It's simply going, see, the HOA would say, well, you know Mr. Gonzalez, your trash can got left out an extra day.

34:35.385 --> 34:38.348
We're going to have to find you because it makes the neighborhood look bad.

34:40.731 --> 34:44.434
A good neighbor would say, hey Jim, hey Mr. Gonzalez.

34:45.410 --> 34:46.832
I noticed your trash can was out.

34:46.892 --> 34:47.834
Can I bring it up for you?

34:49.436 --> 34:50.358
I know you're busy.

34:50.378 --> 34:51.119
I know you got kids.

34:51.159 --> 34:53.342
I know, listen, I'm already grabbing mine.

34:53.402 --> 34:55.585
Can I just, can I throw it up there for you too?

34:56.827 --> 34:57.508
That's a good neighbor.

34:58.370 --> 35:00.333
That's all we're talking about, you know?

35:01.575 --> 35:04.439
Oh, I heard Mrs. Johnson is down with a cold.

35:06.582 --> 35:07.964
Hey, can I bring over a casserole?

35:10.208 --> 35:11.610
Can I bring over a little dish?

35:11.690 --> 35:14.354
Can I bring, you know, can I drive you to the doctor?

35:15.138 --> 35:16.380
Can I pick you up from the doctor?

35:16.880 --> 35:19.404
Little things, it doesn't have to be great big things.

35:22.288 --> 35:29.137
The point is to build genuine relationships that move beyond the surface level interactions.

35:29.598 --> 35:31.160
Hey Bill, hey Tom.

35:35.105 --> 35:41.714
And that's all you know about your neighbor is that their name is Bill or Tom or Mr. Gonzalez or Mrs. Johnson or whatever it is.

35:45.730 --> 35:58.242
Romans 12, 10, we go back a verse, says that we're to love each other with genuine affection and take delight and honor in each other.

36:02.986 --> 36:04.888
We have lots of ways that we can do this.

36:04.948 --> 36:15.058
And so over the next little bit, this is our last, if you will, sub-series for this year in the We Are series.

36:15.746 --> 36:19.975
But we're going to spend some time talking about what it is to be a good neighbor.

36:20.797 --> 36:21.799
This is important.

36:22.801 --> 36:30.738
It's so important to me because I believe as I said in our opening, I believe it's important to Jesus.

36:31.810 --> 36:34.094
Because in scripture, we have two big things.

36:34.114 --> 36:35.937
We have the great commandment and the great commission.

36:36.237 --> 36:39.763
We've talked a lot about the great commission to go make disciples, right?

36:39.783 --> 36:48.498
This is a crux of who we are and we get excited when we talk about going and making disciples and that's something we can be passionate about.

36:48.718 --> 36:54.527
But for most of us, we tend to forget about this that we call the great commandment.

36:55.289 --> 36:58.514
So we have the great commandment and we have the great commission.

36:59.138 --> 37:06.489
The two of those are our pillars, our foundation stones, our base pillars for everything else that we do.

37:06.529 --> 37:12.117
If we don't love our neighbor, it doesn't matter how much you do or go or bid.

37:12.498 --> 37:16.724
I don't care how many cakes you bake or how many outreach events you do.

37:16.744 --> 37:18.487
If you don't love the people, they're gonna know.

37:18.527 --> 37:28.882
And if you're not willing to disciple them, then it's irrelevant how much you witness to them.

37:29.154 --> 37:30.456
We're setting pillars.

37:31.037 --> 37:31.337
Why?

37:31.738 --> 37:38.066
Because three years ago, when we came to the church and we all began, we said, this is new wine.

37:38.106 --> 37:40.469
This is a new dispensation.

37:40.710 --> 37:41.731
It's a new day.

37:41.791 --> 37:50.343
And we're setting a path that God has called us to, that God has set us on for a new season.

37:51.584 --> 37:53.006
But we have to have the pillars.

37:53.046 --> 37:55.730
We have to have the right starting point.

37:57.634 --> 38:08.248
And if we love the Lord with all of our heart, and we love our neighbor as ourself, then everything else is covered.

38:08.849 --> 38:09.871
It's supported.

38:10.371 --> 38:14.737
It's undergirded with what Jesus has asked us to do.

38:15.298 --> 38:26.994
So as we close today, I want us to just dig in, and I hope that you're excited about being

38:27.298 --> 38:28.039
good neighbors.

38:28.460 --> 38:48.659
I hope that you're excited about being somebody who doesn't just take a sermon and let it be a check-off and let it just kind of be, but that we would be a people who take what we're talking about week after week after week as we talk about what it is to be a good neighbor.

38:48.879 --> 38:50.322
When we talk about, okay,

38:50.498 --> 38:52.320
We are assemblies of God.

38:52.440 --> 38:56.345
We believe in, and we had 16 things that we said we believe in.

38:56.686 --> 38:59.689
We believe in the power and the presence of the Holy Spirit.

38:59.709 --> 39:03.634
We believe that there is gonna be power when the Holy Spirit comes upon us.

39:03.894 --> 39:19.794
We believe that Jesus is the Son of God, that he rose on the third day, that he is in heaven, and he is one day gonna come back, and he is gonna take his people, and we are gonna live with him forever in heaven for eternity, amen.

39:21.570 --> 39:32.960
And we believe that we are a church that not only are we an assemblies of God church, but we're a church that is filled with good church members that knows each one of us has a plan and a purpose.

39:32.980 --> 39:34.581
Each one of us has a role.

39:34.601 --> 39:37.444
Each one of us is part of the body that is connected.

39:37.664 --> 39:51.556
Each one of us has a place where we need to stand in the gap because a hand can't be connected to the body if it doesn't have an arm, a foot can't be connected to the body if it doesn't have a leg, a head can't be without a neck.

39:51.536 --> 40:21.426
and so on and so forth, that we all have a plan and a part, and we are part of the health and the wealth of what it is to be Berea Temple, to be the church, that we are not being served, but we are here to serve, that we are not paying our country club dues, but we are paying our tithe back to the God who gave to us, and that he in turn is using that to reach other people, that we are an assemblies of God, church members,

40:21.986 --> 40:25.634
who offer hope and healing to our community.

40:26.215 --> 40:29.864
Because friends, if we're not offering hope and healing, we're doing it wrong.

40:30.725 --> 40:41.810
We might as well close the doors, call it good, lock it up, and be moved on to something as we are able to be the hands and feet of Jesus.

40:43.106 --> 40:44.508
to a lost and dying world.

40:44.829 --> 40:49.156
We are able to communicate what it is that God has for this city.

40:49.437 --> 40:55.307
We are able to stand in the gap when there are inequities, when there are difficulties.

40:55.387 --> 40:58.633
We are able to reach across aisles politically.

40:58.873 --> 41:04.082
We are able to put an arm around somebody that looks, smells, acts,

41:04.354 --> 41:09.559
differently than us and not care because they are our brother or our sister in Christ.

41:09.899 --> 41:12.902
That is who we are building as a Berea temple.

41:13.142 --> 41:19.388
And then we are now an Assemblies of God church who offers hope and healing.

41:20.830 --> 41:22.571
Because we know how to be a good neighbor.

41:22.972 --> 41:28.517
We know how to exist in our community like the good Samaritan.

41:30.098 --> 41:33.842
Who says, I don't see a broken down person that

41:34.082 --> 41:36.284
I need to pass by on the other side.

41:36.645 --> 41:43.292
I see somebody that I need to reach down and I need to kneel down and I need to set aside my own schedule and my own agenda.

41:43.312 --> 41:52.802
And I need to be Jesus today to this person because if I'm Jesus to this person today, then Jesus will allow somebody else to fill the gap where I'm having to push aside.

41:55.946 --> 41:56.867
This is the church.

41:58.148 --> 41:59.510
This is what we're called to.

42:00.511 --> 42:03.474
This is the action, the active

42:05.282 --> 42:07.224
presence of what we're supposed to be.

42:09.126 --> 42:10.888
We are the Church of Jesus Christ.

42:12.169 --> 42:13.130
We are the body.

42:14.411 --> 42:16.033
And we are His hands and feet.

42:17.074 --> 42:18.075
So Father, we thank You.

42:18.395 --> 42:19.056
We praise You.

42:20.798 --> 42:23.761
Lord, there are so many things that we need to do in this world.

42:25.502 --> 42:26.784
But God, we need to love You.

42:28.746 --> 42:33.170
And we tend to do a pretty okay job of that.

42:34.946 --> 42:37.910
Maybe we don't do quite as good a job of loving our neighbors ourselves.

42:41.594 --> 42:49.284
But God, we ask that you would help us as a church, to move past any barriers that might be in the way.

42:51.827 --> 43:00.498
That you would help us, God, to be your hands and feet, to be good neighbors.

43:04.482 --> 43:08.429
We're going to close with our closing song if you need prayer, if you need a touch.

43:09.851 --> 43:13.798
We're not going to make a specific altar call today, but the altars are open if you need to pray.

43:14.239 --> 43:23.154
As we close out, once our song is finished, we'll close in a closing prayer and we'll be dismissed.

